This paper deals with functional logic programming languages, which are a subfield of programming languages (cs.PL). It also discusses the meaning of equality in these languages, which is a topic in logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper introduces a new type class and discusses its implications on program optimization, which are topics in software engineering (cs.SE) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with algebraic data types, which are a common concept in functional programming (cs.FL).
